  <chapter number="16" style="c" sid="1CO 16" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="1CO 16:1" />Concerning the matter of taking up a collection for the poor<char style="it"> and sending it </char>to
        God’s people<char style="sup">[a]</char> <char style="it">in Jerusalem</char>, do the same thing that
        I commanded the churches in Galatia to do: <verse eid="1CO 16:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="1CO 16:2" />Let each of you in private stash away <char style="it">a bit of your money</char> every Sunday<char style="sup">[b]</char>—whatever
        you can afford—so that when I come, there won’t be any collection-taking going on then. <verse eid="1CO 16:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="1CO 16:3" />When I make it over to your place, whomever you happen to decide upon to write letters of recommendation
        for, I’ll dispatch as couriers to take your gift to Jerusalem. <verse eid="1CO 16:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="1CO 16:4" />If there happens to be <char style="it">an issue of </char>respect<char style="sup">[A]</char>, they’ll
        come with me <char style="it">when I depart</char>.<verse eid="1CO 16:4" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="1CO 16:5" />I’ll come your way when I pass through Macedonia; I’ll be passing through Macedonia, you see. <verse eid="1CO 16:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="1CO 16:6" />Perhaps I’ll stay with you <char style="it">a while </char>or even spend the winter, so that you’ll send
        me on my way <char style="it">refreshed and prepared for the journey</char><char style="sup">[B]</char>
        wherever I happen to go; <verse eid="1CO 16:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="1CO 16:7" />you see, at the moment I don’t want to <char style="it">just </char>stop by for a short visit while passing
        through the area; you see, I hope to stay a while with you, if the Lord permits. <verse eid="1CO 16:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="1CO 16:8" />I’ll stay in Ephesus until Pentecost (i.e., until late May to early June). <verse eid="1CO 16:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="1CO 16:9" />In fact, a great door (i.e., a tremendous opportunity) has been opened for me and it looks promising,
        but <char style="it">I’ll have to face</char> many adversaries.<verse eid="1CO 16:9" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="1CO 16:10" />If Timothy happens to show up, see to it that he doesn’t get to where he’s intimidated by you<char style="sup">[c]</char>;
        he’s doing the Lord’s work like I’m doing, you see, <verse eid="1CO 16:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="1CO 16:11" />so don’t let anyone treat him disrespectfully or despise him. Send him forth to his next destination
        in peace (i.e., take care of him, treat him well, and send him out prepared for the journey), so that
        he manages to come to me, for I expect him with the <char style="it">group of </char>comrades<char style="sup">[d]</char>
        <char style="it">who’ll be coming</char>.<verse eid="1CO 16:11" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="1CO 16:12" />Concerning Comrade Apollos…I’ve encouraged him an awful lot to pay you a visit, doing so by travelling
        with the comrades <char style="it">who’ll be coming</char>, and it wasn’t his desire altogether to go
        at this time, but he’ll go in good time.<verse eid="1CO 16:12" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="1CO 16:13" />Stay focused<char style="sup">[e]</char>, take a firm stand in the faith, man up, seize control and hold
        on tightly. <verse eid="1CO 16:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="1CO 16:14" />Let everything you do manifest itself in love.<verse eid="1CO 16:14" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="1CO 16:15" />I appeal to you, comrades…you know first-hand Stephanas’s household, since they’re the crème de la crème
        <char style="it">of the</char> <char style="it">converts</char><char style="sup">[f]</char> of Achaia
        and have been put in positions of deacons for God’s people, the saints…<verse eid="1CO 16:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="1CO 16:16" /><char style="it">I appeal to you</char> that you too would submit to such <char style="it">fine individuals
        </char>as these and to all the fellow-workers and laborers. <verse eid="1CO 16:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="1CO 16:17" />I’m so glad that Stephanas, Fortunatus, and Achaicus showed up, that these fellows filled in the pieces
        that you’re missing<char style="sup">[g]</char>: <verse eid="1CO 16:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="1CO 16:18" />they gave rest to my spirit and to yours, so recognize <char style="it">the character and contribution
        of</char> men such as these.<verse eid="1CO 16:18" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="1CO 16:19" />The churches in <char style="it">the Roman province of </char>Asia send their greetings to you. Aquila
        and Priscilla send many greetings to you in the Lord and are joined in their greetings with the group
        of Christians who meet in their house. <verse eid="1CO 16:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="1CO 16:20" />All the comrades greet you. Give each other a hearty handshake and an affectionate hug—holy ones—<char
        style="it">for me.</char><char style="sup">[h]</char><verse eid="1CO 16:20" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="1CO 16:21" />The greeting <char style="it">written here </char>is in my own handwriting, that of Paul’s. <verse eid="1CO 16:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="1CO 16:22" />If anyone doesn’t like the Lord a lot<char style="sup">[i]</char>, let him be accursed. Maranatha (Do
        come Lord).<verse eid="1CO 16:22" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="1CO 16:23" />The grace of the Lord Jesus <char style="it">be </char>with you all. <verse eid="1CO 16:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="1CO 16:24" /><char style="it">May </char>my love <char style="it">be</char> with all of you in Christ Jesus.<verse eid="1CO 16:24" />
    </para>
